{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><div class=\"chapter-heading\"><h1>Creature Types</h1><figure class=\"chapter-number\"><figcaption><span>Savage Ebrron</span></figcaption></figure></div><div><p class=\"drop-cap\">This selection of creatures and monsters details the special abilities possessed by the monsters your heroes must fight. Also included are some commonly occurring beasts of Golarion. You'll find dozens more exotic and dangerous fearsome foes in the <cite>Savage Eberron</cite> Bestiary.</p><p>This Bestiary categorizes creatures within Fifteen distinct Types. These categories are referenced in other <em>Savage Eberron</em> rules.</p><ul><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Aberration:</span> Rare creatures with bizarre anatomy, strange abilities, or other alien characteristics.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Animal:</span> Any living vertebrate creature with no magical abilities and no innate language or culture. Smarts is relative to the animal world, as indicated by the (A) as a reminder of “animal intelligence.”</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Construct:</span> An artificially created object or creature.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Dragon:</span> The family of legendary magical reptilian creatures, usually winged.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Elemental:</span> A creature that exists as the purest form of the basic elements: earth, air, water, and fire. Elementals are self-aware and intelligent entities and were made up of matter from their land.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Fey:</span> Supernatural creatures, usually humanoid in appearance, with connections to nature or some other fantastical realm.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Giant:</span> Biped creature, with a human-like head, torso and limbs that tower over humanoids with immense strength and toughness.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Humanoid:</span> Biped creatures, with a human-like head, torso and limbs. Humanoids usually possess language and form cultures.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Magical Beast:</span> Similar to Animals, creatures of this type possess some kind of magical or supernatural ability.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Monstrous Humanoid</span>: Similar to Humanoids, these creatures have some monstrous features or characteristics, as well as magical or beastly abilities.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Ooze:</span> Mindless amorphous creatures, Oozes often consume resources and pose environmental hazards to other creature types.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Outsider:</span> Although these creatures resemble other types, their origin, or perhaps their composition, comes from beyond the Material Plane.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Plant:</span> Creatures composed of vegetation, different than regular plant life, which are considered objects.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Undead:</span> A once-living creature reanimated by magical or supernatural force.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Vermin:</span> Living invertebrate creatures, from insects, to arachnids, and arthropods.</li></ul></div></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ltavh0xcxs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules","color":"#008000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675288716064,"modifiedTime":1676930950065,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"uTC39JtCE6QE0uGb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
